description:
&lt;p&gt;As part of the Innovation &amp; Intelligent Automation team, we are recruiting talented intelligent automation experts to scale and accelerate the deployment of automation in the Trust and wider health and care community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the opportunity to work with highly complex automation projects and will be part of a team creating world-class automation solutions across clinical and corporate areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role of Automation Analyst is pivotal to our success and vision, we are looking for a driven individual, who is excited by daily challenges and thrive in a busy and ever-changing environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an individual who can promote and embed Digital Automation skills within the wider clinical and corporate teams to ensure its widespread transformation benefit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This person will be responsible for the operational support of the Trust’s Robotic Process Automation environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Primarily through the use of cloud-based automation tools and software, this post will assist the Trust in the delivery of cost-effective, risk-controlled, robust, reliable, responsive and secure automation solutions to assist the organisation in eliminating paper and improving efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One of the primary functions is to operationally support the automation platform but will also participate in all areas of the robotic automation development lifecycle including design, programming, versioning control, testing, documentation, technical implementation and deployment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Finally, you will bring a high level of expertise, and a passion for supporting the goals and ambitions of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: James Davis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Director of Innovation&lt;/p&gt;
